File: Rugby balls JOHANNESBURG - The Sharks have beefed up their technical team ahead of the start of the inaugural United Rugby Championship. With coach Sean Everitt committing to a long-term deal, the Durban side has also roped in Noel McNamara as attack coach with John McFarland taking over as defence coach. READ: Springbok hooker Mbonambi to leave Stormers for Sharks The biggest addition is Blitzboks coach Neil Powell who is poised to join the Sharks after the 2022 Sevens World Cup. Powell will replace McFarland as defence coach after leading Springbok Sevens to both the Tokyo Olympics and next year's Sevens World Cup. Etienne Fynn and Phiwe Nomlomo will retain their forwards and skills roles in the senior setup.